===Etymology===
From {{L.}} {{term|absinthium|lang=la}} < {{AGr.}} {{term|sc=polytonic|ἀψίνθιον|tr=apsinthion|lang=grc}}.  The Ancient Greek word is of uncertain origin. May be from {{Pers.}} {{term|sc=fa-Arab|اسپند|tr=ispand||wild rue|lang=fa}}. See also [[w:Absinthe#Etymology|Absinthe on Wikipedia]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{botany}} The common [[wormwood]] (''[[Artemisia]] absinthium''), an [[intensely]] bitter herb used in the production of [[absinthe]] and [[vermouth]], and as a [[tonic]].

